"{\"uid\": \"mondaq.com-unitedstates-employee-rights-labour-relations-1501770-2024-summer-olympics-series-australia\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"The 2024 Summer Olympic Games began Friday, July 26.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 52, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The 2024 Summer Olympic Games\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 29}, {\"ngram\": \"July\", \"from\": 44, \"to\": 48}]}, {\"sentence\": \"To celebrate this international event, Littler offices around the globe will share key changes in labor and employment laws that have transpired since the last time their countries hosted the Olympic games.1 The last time that Australia hosted the Olympics was in 2000 in Sydney.\", \"from\": 53, \"to\": 338, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 285, \"end\": 294, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prime_Minister_of_Australia\", \"score\": 0.6732478855037166, \"rank\": 0.48533700815093234, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prime_Minister_of_Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prime_Minister_of_Australia\"}, {\"begin\": 331, \"end\": 337, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 0.999713164417807, \"rank\": 0.000284025364866432, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this international event\", \"from\": 66, \"to\": 90}, {\"ngram\": \"Littler offices\", \"from\": 92, \"to\": 107}, {\"ngram\": \"the globe\", \"from\": 115, \"to\": 124}, {\"ngram\": \"key changes\", \"from\": 136, \"to\": 147}, {\"ngram\": \"labor and employment laws\", \"from\": 151, \"to\": 176}, {\"ngram\": \"the last time\", \"from\": 204, \"to\": 217}, {\"ngram\": \"their countries\", \"from\": 218, \"to\": 233}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic games.1\", \"from\": 241, \"to\": 260}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 297, \"to\": 309}, {\"ngram\": \"Sydney\", \"from\": 325, \"to\": 331}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At that time, the Workplace Relations Act 1996 (Cth) was in place.\", \"from\": 339, \"to\": 406, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"that time\", \"from\": 342, \"to\": 351}, {\"ngram\": \"the Workplace Relations Act\", \"from\": 353, \"to\": 380}, {\"ngram\": \"Cth\", \"from\": 387, \"to\": 390}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 399, \"to\": 404}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That Act was repealed following the election of a Labor Government in 2007, after 11 years of a Liberal (conservative) government in Australia.\", \"from\": 407, \"to\": 552, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 542, \"end\": 551, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prime_Minister_of_Australia\", \"score\": 0.6732478855037166, \"rank\": 0.48533700815093234, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prime_Minister_of_Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prime_Minister_of_Australia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"That Act\", \"from\": 407, \"to\": 415}, {\"ngram\": \"the election\", \"from\": 439, \"to\": 451}, {\"ngram\": \"a Labor Government\", \"from\": 455, \"to\": 473}, {\"ngram\": \"11 years\", \"from\": 489, \"to\": 497}, {\"ngram\": \"a Liberal (conservative) government\", \"from\": 501, \"to\": 536}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With the repeal of the Workplace Relations Act 1996 (Cth) came the introduction of theFair Work Act(FW Act), which today remains the primary Commonwealth legislation regulating employment and workplace relations.\", \"from\": 553, \"to\": 768, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 696, \"end\": 708, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Government\", \"score\": 0.9999999982237568, \"rank\": 1.1989192998319103e-09, \"text\": \"Commonwealth\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Government\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Government\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the repeal\", \"from\": 558, \"to\": 568}, {\"ngram\": \"the Workplace Relations Act\", \"from\": 572, \"to\": 599}, {\"ngram\": \"Cth\", \"from\": 606, \"to\": 609}, {\"ngram\": \"the introduction\", \"from\": 616, \"to\": 632}, {\"ngram\": \"theFair Work Act(FW Act\", \"from\": 636, \"to\": 659}, {\"ngram\": \"employment\", \"from\": 730, \"to\": 740}, {\"ngram\": \"workplace relations\", \"from\": 745, \"to\": 764}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Most provisions of the FW Act took effect on July 1, 2009.\", \"from\": 769, \"to\": 828, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Most provisions\", \"from\": 769, \"to\": 784}, {\"ngram\": \"the FW Act\", \"from\": 788, \"to\": 798}, {\"ngram\": \"effect\", \"from\": 804, \"to\": 810}, {\"ngram\": \"July\", \"from\": 814, \"to\": 818}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The introduction of the FW Act was one of the most significant reforms to Australia's employment laws in the country's history and (among other things) saw the introduction of the statutory modern award system.\", \"from\": 830, \"to\": 1043, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 905, \"end\": 914, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prime_Minister_of_Australia\", \"score\": 0.6732478855037166, \"rank\": 0.48533700815093234, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prime_Minister_of_Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prime_Minister_of_Australia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The introduction\", \"from\": 830, \"to\": 846}, {\"ngram\": \"the FW Act\", \"from\": 850, \"to\": 860}, {\"ngram\": \"the most significant reforms\", \"from\": 872, \"to\": 900}, {\"ngram\": \"the country's history\", \"from\": 935, \"to\": 956}, {\"ngram\": \"other things\", \"from\": 968, \"to\": 980}, {\"ngram\": \"the introduction\", \"from\": 986, \"to\": 1002}, {\"ngram\": \"the statutory modern award system\", \"from\": 1006, \"to\": 1039}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The FW Act establishes a safety net comprising: the National Employment Standards (NES), modern awards and national minimum wage orders, and a compliance and enforcement regime.\", \"from\": 1044, \"to\": 1224, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1097, \"end\": 1126, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Employment_Standards\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"National Employment Standards\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Employment_Standards\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Employment_Standards\"}, {\"begin\": 1128, \"end\": 1131, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nintendo_Entertainment_System\", \"score\": 0.9999855941797164, \"rank\": 1.4405778813718811e-05, \"text\": \"NES\", \"types\": [\"Q1067263\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nintendo_Entertainment_System\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nintendo_Entertainment_System\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The FW Act\", \"from\": 1044, \"to\": 1054}, {\"ngram\": \"a safety net comprising\", \"from\": 1067, \"to\": 1090}, {\"ngram\": \"modern awards\", \"from\": 1133, \"to\": 1146}, {\"ngram\": \"national minimum wage orders\", \"from\": 1151, \"to\": 1179}, {\"ngram\": \"a compliance and enforcement regime\", \"from\": 1185, \"to\": 1220}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A modern award (award) is a legal document that sets out the minimum terms and conditions of employment on top of the NES.\", \"from\": 1226, \"to\": 1349, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1345, \"end\": 1348, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nintendo_Entertainment_System\", \"score\": 0.9999855941797164, \"rank\": 1.4405778813718811e-05, \"text\": \"NES\", \"types\": [\"Q1067263\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nintendo_Entertainment_System\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nintendo_Entertainment_System\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A modern award\", \"from\": 1226, \"to\": 1240}, {\"ngram\": \"award\", \"from\": 1242, \"to\": 1247}, {\"ngram\": \"a legal document\", \"from\": 1252, \"to\": 1268}, {\"ngram\": \"the minimum terms\", \"from\": 1283, \"to\": 1300}, {\"ngram\": \"conditions\", \"from\": 1305, \"to\": 1315}, {\"ngram\": \"employment\", \"from\": 1319, \"to\": 1329}, {\"ngram\": \"top\", \"from\": 1333, \"to\": 1336}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Modern awards came into effect on January 1, 2010.\", \"from\": 1351, \"to\": 1401, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Modern awards\", \"from\": 1351, \"to\": 1364}, {\"ngram\": \"effect\", \"from\": 1375, \"to\": 1381}, {\"ngram\": \"January\", \"from\": 1385, \"to\": 1392}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Awards provide entitlements including pay, hours of work, rosters, breaks, allowances, penalty, rates, and overtime.\", \"from\": 1402, \"to\": 1520, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Awards\", \"from\": 1402, \"to\": 1408}, {\"ngram\": \"entitlements\", \"from\": 1417, \"to\": 1429}, {\"ngram\": \"pay\", \"from\": 1440, \"to\": 1443}, {\"ngram\": \"hours\", \"from\": 1445, \"to\": 1450}, {\"ngram\": \"work\", \"from\": 1454, \"to\": 1458}, {\"ngram\": \"rosters\", \"from\": 1460, \"to\": 1467}, {\"ngram\": \"breaks\", \"from\": 1469, \"to\": 1475}, {\"ngram\": \"allowances\", \"from\": 1477, \"to\": 1487}, {\"ngram\": \"penalty\", \"from\": 1489, \"to\": 1496}, {\"ngram\": \"rates\", \"from\": 1498, \"to\": 1503}, {\"ngram\": \"overtime\", \"from\": 1509, \"to\": 1517}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Modern awards are industry- or occupation-based and apply to employers and employees who perform work covered by the award.\", \"from\": 1521, \"to\": 1646, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Modern awards\", \"from\": 1521, \"to\": 1534}, {\"ngram\": \"employers\", \"from\": 1582, \"to\": 1591}, {\"ngram\": \"employees\", \"from\": 1596, \"to\": 1605}, {\"ngram\": \"work\", \"from\": 1618, \"to\": 1622}, {\"ngram\": \"the award\", \"from\": 1634, \"to\": 1643}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There are more than 100 industry or occupation awards that cover most people who work in Australia.\", \"from\": 1647, \"to\": 1748, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1738, \"end\": 1747, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prime_Minister_of_Australia\", \"score\": 0.6732478855037166, \"rank\": 0.48533700815093234, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prime_Minister_of_Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prime_Minister_of_Australia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"more than 100 industry or occupation awards\", \"from\": 1657, \"to\": 1700}, {\"ngram\": \"most people\", \"from\": 1712, \"to\": 1723}]}, {\"sentence\": \"An employer can be covered by more than one award, depending on the jobs the employees do.\", \"from\": 1749, \"to\": 1840, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"An employer\", \"from\": 1749, \"to\": 1760}, {\"ngram\": \"more than one award\", \"from\": 1779, \"to\": 1798}, {\"ngram\": \"the jobs\", \"from\": 1813, \"to\": 1821}, {\"ngram\": \"the employees\", \"from\": 1822, \"to\": 1835}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Since the introduction of the modern award system, there have been significant amendments to the industry and occupation awards that are in effect and apply to a significant number of Australian employers.\", \"from\": 1842, \"to\": 2050, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2028, \"end\": 2038, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Government\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2309438207551657e-14, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Government\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Government\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the introduction\", \"from\": 1848, \"to\": 1864}, {\"ngram\": \"the modern award system\", \"from\": 1868, \"to\": 1891}, {\"ngram\": \"significant amendments\", \"from\": 1909, \"to\": 1931}, {\"ngram\": \"the industry and occupation awards\", \"from\": 1935, \"to\": 1969}, {\"ngram\": \"effect\", \"from\": 1982, \"to\": 1988}, {\"ngram\": \"a significant number\", \"from\": 2002, \"to\": 2022}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, in this Olympic year we are set to see yet another significant reform with the pending introduction of criminal penalties for modern award breaches.\", \"from\": 2051, \"to\": 2210, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this Olympic year\", \"from\": 2063, \"to\": 2080}, {\"ngram\": \"yet another significant reform\", \"from\": 2099, \"to\": 2129}, {\"ngram\": \"the pending introduction\", \"from\": 2135, \"to\": 2159}, {\"ngram\": \"criminal penalties\", \"from\": 2163, \"to\": 2181}, {\"ngram\": \"modern award breaches\", \"from\": 2186, \"to\": 2207}]}, {\"sentence\": \"TheFair Work Legislation Amendment (Closing Loopholes) Act 2023introduces a number of workplace changes, some of which have already taken effect as of late 2023 and during the first half of 2024.\", \"from\": 2212, \"to\": 2410, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Closing Loopholes\", \"from\": 2248, \"to\": 2265}, {\"ngram\": \"a number\", \"from\": 2286, \"to\": 2294}, {\"ngram\": \"workplace changes\", \"from\": 2298, \"to\": 2315}, {\"ngram\": \"effect\", \"from\": 2350, \"to\": 2356}, {\"ngram\": \"the first half\", \"from\": 2384, \"to\": 2398}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Further amendments will apply from August 2024 or in early 2025, including amendments addressing the following: One of the most noteworthy upcoming changes is the criminalizing of wage underpayments.\", \"from\": 2411, \"to\": 2613, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Further amendments\", \"from\": 2411, \"to\": 2429}, {\"ngram\": \"August\", \"from\": 2446, \"to\": 2452}, {\"ngram\": \"amendments\", \"from\": 2486, \"to\": 2496}, {\"ngram\": \"the following\", \"from\": 2508, \"to\": 2521}, {\"ngram\": \"the most noteworthy upcoming changes\", \"from\": 2530, \"to\": 2566}, {\"ngram\": \"the criminalizing\", \"from\": 2570, \"to\": 2587}, {\"ngram\": \"wage underpayments\", \"from\": 2591, \"to\": 2609}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This means intentional underpayment of wages by employers will become a criminal offence in certain circumstances.\", \"from\": 2614, \"to\": 2730, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"intentional underpayment\", \"from\": 2625, \"to\": 2649}, {\"ngram\": \"wages\", \"from\": 2653, \"to\": 2658}, {\"ngram\": \"employers\", \"from\": 2662, \"to\": 2671}, {\"ngram\": \"a criminal offence\", \"from\": 2684, \"to\": 2702}, {\"ngram\": \"certain circumstances\", \"from\": 2706, \"to\": 2727}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Employers will commit an offence if: The wage theft offence will carry a maximum of 10 years' imprisonment, and/or a maximum fine of the greater of: Another noteworthy change for employers to be aware of in this Olympic year is the new right to disconnect law, which is a mere two months away from implementation.\", \"from\": 2731, \"to\": 3049, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Employers\", \"from\": 2731, \"to\": 2740}, {\"ngram\": \"an offence\", \"from\": 2753, \"to\": 2763}, {\"ngram\": \"The wage theft offence\", \"from\": 2768, \"to\": 2790}, {\"ngram\": \"a maximum\", \"from\": 2802, \"to\": 2811}, {\"ngram\": \"10 years' imprisonment\", \"from\": 2815, \"to\": 2837}, {\"ngram\": \"a maximum fine\", \"from\": 2846, \"to\": 2860}, {\"ngram\": \"Another noteworthy change\", \"from\": 2880, \"to\": 2905}, {\"ngram\": \"employers\", \"from\": 2910, \"to\": 2919}, {\"ngram\": \"this Olympic year\", \"from\": 2938, \"to\": 2955}, {\"ngram\": \"the new right\", \"from\": 2959, \"to\": 2972}, {\"ngram\": \"law\", \"from\": 2987, \"to\": 2990}, {\"ngram\": \"implementation\", \"from\": 3029, \"to\": 3043}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The new law will provide eligible employees with the right to refuse employer or third-party contact (including attempted contact) outside of working hours unless that refusal is unreasonable.\", \"from\": 3050, \"to\": 3245, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The new law\", \"from\": 3050, \"to\": 3061}, {\"ngram\": \"eligible employees\", \"from\": 3075, \"to\": 3093}, {\"ngram\": \"the right\", \"from\": 3099, \"to\": 3108}, {\"ngram\": \"employer\", \"from\": 3119, \"to\": 3127}, {\"ngram\": \"third-party contact\", \"from\": 3131, \"to\": 3150}, {\"ngram\": \"attempted contact\", \"from\": 3162, \"to\": 3179}, {\"ngram\": \"working hours\", \"from\": 3192, \"to\": 3205}, {\"ngram\": \"that refusal\", \"from\": 3213, \"to\": 3225}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In determining whether an employee's refusal is unreasonable, several factors will be considered, including but not limited to: In the event of a dispute, if the employer and the employee are unable to resolve it after discussion, either party can go to theFair Work Commission(the Australian national workplace relations tribunal) for dispute resolution.\", \"from\": 3246, \"to\": 3607, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3533, \"end\": 3543, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Government\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2309438207551657e-14, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Government\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Government\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an employee's refusal\", \"from\": 3269, \"to\": 3290}, {\"ngram\": \"several factors\", \"from\": 3308, \"to\": 3323}, {\"ngram\": \"the event\", \"from\": 3377, \"to\": 3386}, {\"ngram\": \"a dispute\", \"from\": 3390, \"to\": 3399}, {\"ngram\": \"the employer\", \"from\": 3404, \"to\": 3416}, {\"ngram\": \"the employee\", \"from\": 3421, \"to\": 3433}, {\"ngram\": \"discussion\", \"from\": 3465, \"to\": 3475}, {\"ngram\": \"either party\", \"from\": 3477, \"to\": 3489}, {\"ngram\": \"dispute resolution\", \"from\": 3582, \"to\": 3600}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All modern awards will include a right to disconnect term by August 26, 2024, adding specific rules to awards to ensure the new terms reflect the realities of the occupation and industry.\", \"from\": 3609, \"to\": 3798, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"All modern awards\", \"from\": 3609, \"to\": 3626}, {\"ngram\": \"a right\", \"from\": 3640, \"to\": 3647}, {\"ngram\": \"term\", \"from\": 3662, \"to\": 3666}, {\"ngram\": \"August\", \"from\": 3670, \"to\": 3676}, {\"ngram\": \"specific rules\", \"from\": 3694, \"to\": 3708}, {\"ngram\": \"awards\", \"from\": 3712, \"to\": 3718}, {\"ngram\": \"the new terms\", \"from\": 3729, \"to\": 3742}, {\"ngram\": \"the realities\", \"from\": 3751, \"to\": 3764}, {\"ngram\": \"the occupation\", \"from\": 3768, \"to\": 3782}, {\"ngram\": \"industry\", \"from\": 3787, \"to\": 3795}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We recommend that employers act promptly to review their pay practices, policies, and employment agreements to comply with the new laws ahead of August.\", \"from\": 3800, \"to\": 3954, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"employers\", \"from\": 3818, \"to\": 3827}, {\"ngram\": \"their pay practices\", \"from\": 3851, \"to\": 3870}, {\"ngram\": \"policies\", \"from\": 3872, \"to\": 3880}, {\"ngram\": \"employment agreements\", \"from\": 3886, \"to\": 3907}, {\"ngram\": \"the new laws\", \"from\": 3923, \"to\": 3935}, {\"ngram\": \"August\", \"from\": 3945, \"to\": 3951}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Footnote 1.\", \"from\": 3956, \"to\": 3968, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Footnote\", \"from\": 3956, \"to\": 3964}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Littler's International Guide discusses more than 90 workplace law topics in over 45 countries/territories, including jurisdictions in every region of the world.\", \"from\": 3969, \"to\": 4132, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Littler's International Guide\", \"from\": 3969, \"to\": 3998}, {\"ngram\": \"more than 90 workplace law topics\", \"from\": 4009, \"to\": 4042}, {\"ngram\": \"over 45 countries/territories\", \"from\": 4046, \"to\": 4075}, {\"ngram\": \"jurisdictions\", \"from\": 4087, \"to\": 4100}, {\"ngram\": \"every region\", \"from\": 4104, \"to\": 4116}, {\"ngram\": \"th